1
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:06,998
Come to my family again
and you and I are at war.

2
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:10,630
- Eat your children!
- No!

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:12,916
Hyde's an animal, I'm dangerous.

4
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:19,479
Hi Honey, I'm home.

5
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:22,108
- Where's my husband?
- Tom's gone Honey.

6
00:00:22,280 --> 00:00:26,512
Tonight is everything this organisation
has worked towards ever since it began.

7
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:33,188
Tonight is the culmination
of over one hundred years of planning.

8
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:38,757
There now, Benjamin,
it'll be over in a moment.

9
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:41,514
Dr Jackman is coming home.

10
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,274
No, for God's sake, no! Please! No!!

11
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:46,954
You won't be needing
this any more. Sorry.

12
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:48,394
Claire! No!

13
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:53,634
Peter, for God's sake,
he has claustrophobia.

14
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:54,800
I know.

15
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:23,591
Sorry, dropped the phone.

16
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,671
What time did you say?

17
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:29,994
You OK in there? Need a refill?

18
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:32,063
No, I'm fine, thanks.

19
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:36,756
That'll be Claire.

20
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:39,480
Hey.

21
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,998
- Hey. Am I late?
- No.

22
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:44,390
- Can I try again?
- Come on, I'm still cooking.

23
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:47,677
Yeah, well, I was trying to be late.

24
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,956
Oh, shit!

25
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,478
Sorry, no offence.

26
00:01:54,472 --> 00:01:55,497
OK.

27
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,080
See ya!

28
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,471
Who asked you to set me up?

29
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,232
Uh, whoever asked you to do that?

30
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,640
- You did.
- Apart from me.

31
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,846
- Good-Iooking, isn't he?
- Didn't notice.

32
00:02:08,966 --> 00:02:11,629
Not my type. Not interested.

33
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,109
And those glasses
are going to have to go.

34
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:16,430
- Damn it!
- Gotcha!

35
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:19,239
I'm going to have to drink now.
I brought my car.

36
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,960
Take these through, talk to him.

37
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:24,156
- God!
- And Claire, don't, you know...

38
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,515
- What?
- You know.

39
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:30,309
- Men like a sense of humour.
- Yeah, theirs. And don't scare him.

40
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,424
Don't be scary,
don't be funny, gotcha.

41
00:02:32,544 --> 00:02:33,916
Don't get onto what he earns.

42
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:36,355
- I don't do that.
- You always do that.

43
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:41,310
No funny, no scary, no money.
How hard can it be?

44
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:43,710
I give her one sentence.

45
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,353
So, what do you do?

46
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,715
Rich men.

47
00:02:58,338 --> 00:03:02,157
Sorry, it's a joke. Sorry.

48
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,520
OK?

49
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:11,879
Yes, er... just, er...

50
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:16,120
...admiring the patio.

51
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,158
Did you have that last time?

52
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:20,320
Yes.

53
00:03:23,526 --> 00:03:24,526
OK.

54
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:29,273
It's nice, though, it's a nice patio.

55
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,469
All right?

56
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,993
- Need any help?
- Do you?

57
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,160
No, no.

58
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,756
All your own work?

59
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:48,359
The garden?

60
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,556
Except the patio.

61
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,510
So, Tom, how's work?

62
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,796
Oh, you know.

63
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,953
Same as ever.

64
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:19,592
- Tom's a research scientist.
- Ah, a scientist, right.

65
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:24,269
What do you do?

66
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:28,634
About 250,000 a year.

67
00:04:31,611 --> 00:04:34,436
Sorry, hang on a minute.

68
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:50,113
- Your cab, I said five minutes.
- So early.

69
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:52,396
Yes, sorry, got a meeting first thing.

70
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,959
What's wrong?

71
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:56,953
- I've lost my shoes.
- How can you lose your shoes?

72
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:59,509
- Did you take them off?
- Obviously.

73
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:03,639
You check the bathroom,
I'll look next door.

74
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,030
Do you always take
your shoes off when you eat?

75
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:13,228
- Yes. Did you hide them?
- Mm-hm.

76
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,400
Why?

77
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,434
You were leaving.

78
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,829
- Oh, my God!
- I know.

79
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,878
- You barely spoke.
- We still haven't.

80
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,395
- Tell me everything. Disgust me.
- Who's that?

81
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,710
- Nobody, my mother, go away.
- OK.

82
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,392
He's up. Later.

83
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:53,791
We've still got his shoes.
Do you want me to send them round?

84
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:55,518
No hurry.

85
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,120
Tom?

86
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,560
Yeah?

87
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,889
<i>Is there a man's dressing gown
in there?</i>

88
00:06:18,427 --> 00:06:19,427
Yes.

89
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,272
I was hoping you wouldn't notice it.

90
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:27,513
Was specifically pointing it out
part of the plan?

91
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:42,316
Old boyfriend?

92
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,994
He is now.

93
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,560
Ah!

94
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:20,433
Twins in the family either of you?

95
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,600
No.

96
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:25,715
Well, there's news on that.
It's twins.

97
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,233
- But we had scans.
- Tom.

98
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:31,598
- The scans were wrong.
- There was one heartbeat.

99
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:01,397
Now bring it to me, that's it,
nice and slow. Careful. Good.

100
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,799
Tell him he's here.

101
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,996
Gemini has landed.

102
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,628
"Gemini"?! For God's sake
who thought that one up?

103
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:12,873
Is that supposed to be clever? And let
go of her, she's not going anywhere.

104
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,998
Claire, I'm sorry, we have
some questions, it may take a while.

105
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,229
Some questions?

106
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,436
I apologise in advance for the coffee.

107
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:22,717
- You have some questions?
- A few, yes.

108
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:26,953
You have my husband in a box!

109
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:29,588
Don't let them hear you call it a box,
the tech boys.

110
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,866
Total self-contained
life-support system.

111
00:08:31,986 --> 00:08:33,958
It's the safest place
in the world, apparently.

112
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:38,113
As long as the batteries don't run out.
Let her go, it's fine.

113
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:44,118
What's that? What's that noise?

114
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,674
He's having a sort of...
Well, a sort of panic attack.

115
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:58,673
Get him downstairs,
let's get him stabilised.

116
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,159
OK. To me guys, come on.

117
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,833
Be careful, though. Slowly.

118
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,116
Uh, Claire, this way.

119
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,672
Mrs Jackman.

120
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:09,752
Maybe you should call me
Mrs Jackman now, what do you think?

121
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,799
Mrs Jackman.

122
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,793
- Morning, Dr Jackman.
- Morning.

123
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,838
- Mrs Jackman all right?
- Fine.

124
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,116
- How was your weekend?
- Twins.

125
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,824
Twins!

126
00:09:57,920 --> 00:10:00,639
Sorry, could you do that
again for me, please?

127
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:13,153
Did I bring the wrong thumb?

128
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,339
How long have they kept you here?

129
00:10:33,459 --> 00:10:35,229
- Idiots.
- Is there a problem?

130
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,675
Only with our equipment.
They'll fire someone.

131
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:42,356
It's an American company,
they like to feel dynamic.

132
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,988
You haven't been down here.
I'll show you to the lift.

133
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:47,993
I didn't know there was a down here.

134
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:56,034
- Who's that?
- Oh, for God's sake!

135
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:00,479
- Who is that?
- Another American. Hard to keep up,

136
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,154
they keep sacking each other.
I don't know their names.

137
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,231
There are women here
you haven't slept with?

138
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:09,279
- Why so many rumours about me?
- Probably all the sex.

139
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:17,070
- Oh, here, use mine.
- That's OK. We have to use mine here.

140
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:21,160
- I thought I'd clearance everywhere.
- You're down the rabbit hole now.

141
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:23,589
Everything you think is wrong.

142
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:32,274
- Sorry, can I take the stairs?
- What's the problem?

143
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,284
I'm sorry,
it's just I have claustrophobia.

144
00:11:34,404 --> 00:11:35,989
I know.

145
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,111
You know where we are I suppose?

146
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:42,716
- Where Tom worked.
- Where you thought Tom worked.

147
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:45,917
- Where he thought he worked.
- Where are we going?

148
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:50,073
Down the rabbit hole,
where everything you think is wrong.

149
00:11:56,080 --> 00:12:01,313
Whatever my husband is, putting him
in a box doesn't make you his friend.

150
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:06,918
I'll tell you what it makes me,
what it makes a lot of people, rich.

151
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,753
Very, very rich.

152
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:25,075
- Oh, Sally.
- Um, I'm... I'm leaving.

153
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:29,392
- Yeah, well, it's late.
- Yeah, no, I'm... I'm leaving

154
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:32,199
and I'm... I'm not working
any notice either.

155
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:37,150
- What... what are these supposed to be?
- Just some notes for tomorrow.

156
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,992
Is it a joke?

157
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:42,789
Is it... Is it... s-sexual?

158
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:45,349
If it is s-sexual,

159
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:49,308
l-I can sue you for... for harassment.

160
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:55,271
Wh... I didn't write these.

161
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,318
It... it's your handwriting.

162
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,600
Yes. Yes it is.

163
00:13:09,101 --> 00:13:10,218
Yes it is.

164
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,879
Mind not on the game, is it?
Fantastic, let's keep going.

165
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:35,359
I need to talk to you.

166
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,876
- So what do you think?
- Of what?

167
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:48,679
- My symptoms.
- Look 'em up on the internet.

168
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:51,274
- You're a doctor.
- Yes, I'm a doctor.

169
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,793
Know what I do with symptoms?

170
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,673
I look 'em up on the internet.

171
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:59,911
It's open.
OK, hair on my arm out of nowhere.

172
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:01,254
How do you explain that?

173
00:14:01,374 --> 00:14:04,437
Easy, you imagined it.
Because it's impossible.

174
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:06,703
OK, my thumb print?

175
00:14:06,823 --> 00:14:09,720
Fault in the machinery,
like they told you.

176
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,789
I don't think
they were telling me the truth.

177
00:14:11,909 --> 00:14:13,270
You imagined that too.

178
00:14:14,772 --> 00:14:16,432
Just push, it's open.

179
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,995
OK, so why am I writing pages
of rubbish to my PA?

180
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,993
- Pages and pages of...
- Yeah, that's... that's my favourite.

181
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:26,152
"I'm coming." Talk about repressed.

182
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:30,108
- Who cracks one off in print?
- Could you take this seriously?

183
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:32,131
Stress, common or garden stress.

184
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:35,469
- I prescribe a holiday.
- For Christ's sake!

185
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:50,158
Where did they go?

186
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:52,072
- Where did who go?
- The door knocked.

187
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:55,915
- It didn't.
- I heard them.

188
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:58,389
Tom, nobody knocked.

189
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:05,837
Three words, ho-li-day.

190
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:18,789
I'll be with you shortly

191
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:22,635
and there'll be somebody
on the door if you want anything.

192
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:26,632
I warned you about the coffee, didn't I?

193
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:33,077
Remember you said "rich"
on the day you took my family,

194
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:37,836
on the day you took my children
and put my husband in a box.

195
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:41,390
Remember you said "rich".

196
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,954
I apologise for the coffee.

197
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:53,360
Hello?

198
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:57,035
- A handful, isn't she?
<i>- Who's this?</i>

199
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,509
And attractive too,
I'm sure you've noticed,

200
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:02,399
but you have an eye
for the ladies, don't you, Mr Syme?

201
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:03,709
Pot, kettle.

202
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:07,111
Although I'm not sure I'd trust you
with the wife of a friend.

203
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:10,317
- Pot, kettle.
<i>- Who is this? Who's speaking?</i>

204
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:12,357
Miranda Callendar, private investigator.

205
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,346
<i>Mrs Jackman paid me
to follow her husband,</i>

206
00:16:14,466 --> 00:16:16,513
your organisation paid me to stop.

207
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:20,912
- Peter, could I have a word with you?
- Sorry, just... Sorry, just one second.

208
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:24,595
<i>And you are Peter Syme,</i>
<i>lifelong friend of Tom Jackman</i>

209
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:28,070
and his principal betrayer
and abductor of his wife.

210
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:30,310
Abductor? What on earth
are you talking about?

211
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,675
I've watched her
being driven into your offices.

212
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:35,195
I'd say it was a pretty
full-on abduction.

213
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:38,716
Although maybe you just lock women up
in your basement, recreationally.

214
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:40,950
- Pot, kettle.
- Min!

215
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:44,032
I haven't the slightest idea
what you're talking about.

216
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,475
There's some woman
called Miranda Callendar,

217
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,915
check her out.
Claims to be a private detective.

218
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:51,116
- Says we paid her off.
- On it.

219
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:52,633
- Peter...
- What is it?

220
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:53,915
- Excuse me...
- Meg...

221
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:56,514
- Peter.
- Take my coat. Thank you. What is it?

222
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:58,989
- Can we go outside?
- Why?

223
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:03,631
Mr Syme, she says
that she wants to speak to my boyfriend.

224
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:08,759
- Yes?
<i>- She's very attractive too.</i>

225
00:17:08,947 --> 00:17:10,471
I am impressed.

226
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,756
What is your secret?
Money or conversation?

227
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,232
Is there a point to this?

228
00:17:14,352 --> 00:17:16,515
<i>I'm outside,
I'd like you to let me in.</i>

229
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,829
And why would I do that?

230
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,151
<i>Because you're a bad boy</i>
<i>and I'm a good detective.</i>

231
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:25,633
<i>- Hello?</i>
<i>- Oh, you are a busy boy, aren't you?</i>

232
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:28,360
<i>- I hope you're taking vitamins.</i>
- What are you doing?

233
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:31,637
<i>- Open up.</i>
- Are you serious?

234
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,431
- Hello?
- You can phone everyone

235
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:41,229
I've ever slept with in the entire
building, you are not coming in here!

236
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,713
Go home, this doesn't work.

237
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,233
<i>I know, but this will.</i>

238
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:50,790
I want to speak to Winston Churchill.

239
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:56,397
Oh, and I don't mean that dreadful MP,
I mean the real one, the war leader.

240
00:17:56,560 --> 00:18:00,951
<i>I want to speak to the real actual</i>
<i>Winston Churchill.</i>

241
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,429
I'm such a fan.

242
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,393
Winston Churchill?

243
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:08,996
If you're lucky, I'll introduce you.

244
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,397
It's the best holiday ever.

245
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:28,074
<i> Your kids are having</i>
<i>a good time too, since you ask </i>

246
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,087
