375
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,912
I've heard a lot about you.

376
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:07,169
I've heard bloody nothing
about you, dear.

377
00:30:07,289 --> 00:30:08,834
I work for your husband.

378
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,514
Do you dress like that
or do you wear clothes?

379
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,318
- I wear clothes.
- Does he notice?

380
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:15,436
Half the time.

381
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:21,437
Everyone here is aware of your
husband's... interesting condition.

382
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:26,310
Great! You all knew. Fantastic!

383
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:29,756
No one think it was worth telling me
I married a werewolf?

384
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:35,233
You didn't marry a werewolf,
Mrs Jackman, you married Dr Jekyll.

385
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,152
Dr Jekyll?

386
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:42,553
Dr Henry Jekyll died
in Edinburgh in 1886.

387
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:46,508
- Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde?
- Yes.

388
00:30:47,980 --> 00:30:50,237
Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde was a story.

389
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:53,358
- No, it wasn't.
- No, it isn't.

390
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:54,522
OK...

391
00:30:55,767 --> 00:30:57,195
Sorry.

392
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:01,672
Just, um...
just trying to catch up here,

393
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,592
just trying to be clear.

394
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,356
- I married Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde?
- Yes, you did.

395
00:31:10,159 --> 00:31:13,832
Come on, seriously?
I'm Mrs Jekyll and Hyde?

396
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,579
Yes, you are.

397
00:31:17,628 --> 00:31:22,959
That's so like a man, isn't it? There's
always something they're not telling you.

398
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:25,759
- "Sorry, should have said, I'm Dracula!"
- This is not a joke.

399
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:29,390
- This is not serious!
- Henry Jekyll died without issue.

400
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:31,551
- He's the last of the Jekyll line.
- Sorry?

401
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:35,076
- That means no children.
- I know what it means!

402
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,753
Tom can't be Jekyll's descendent,

403
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:39,115
because Henry Jekyll had no descendants.

404
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:42,556
- But that doesn't make any sense.
- No, none whatsoever.

405
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:47,432
Um, what has Tom told you
about his parents?

406
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:55,519
He was fostered.
His mother abandoned him.

407
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,395
On a railway platform
in Belfast in 1967,

408
00:31:58,557 --> 00:32:00,276
six months after he was born.

409
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,590
I don't believe that.

410
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:06,036
- You don't think he was abandoned?
- I don't think he was born.

411
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:16,035
Yes? Excuse me.

412
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:20,829
But please,
I don't want to miss anything.

413
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:26,278
<i>- Ready?</i>
- As soon as you say.

414
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:28,795
- Is she there?
