for one of our more esteemed tabloids.

493
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:38,875
You weren't trying to clone
Winston Churchill,

494
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:41,474
you were trying to clone Henry Jekyll.

495
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:44,518
After all those years of failing
to recreate his experiment,

496
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:46,885
you finally decided
to throw in the towel

497
00:41:47,018 --> 00:41:49,310
and recreate the man himself.

498
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:52,830
How am I doing now?

499
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:56,197
It took until 1997 to successfully
clone a sheep.

500
00:41:56,360 --> 00:42:00,035
Do you really imagine in 1965
we were able to clone a dead Victorian?

501
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:04,432
Klein & Utterson were successfully
cloning farm animals in the 1950s.

502
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:07,831
Anyone that tried to speak about it
ended up very rich or disappeared.

503
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,514
- Which are you hoping for?
- Neither.

504
00:42:14,080 --> 00:42:16,548
You think Tom Jackman is a clone?

505
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:20,030
A genetic experiment, grown in a lab?

506
00:42:20,802 --> 00:42:21,802
Yes.

507
00:42:25,864 --> 00:42:26,864
I see.

508
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:35,948
Tell Colonel Hart we'll be needing him.

509
00:42:36,120 --> 00:42:38,350
This is over.

510
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:42,399
- Why?
- Because Tom Jackman is not a clone.

511
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:45,518
You have nothing.

512
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:49,673
You have walked in here with nothing.

513
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:52,274
I'm sorry.

514
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:57,070
- Why are you sorry, Peter?
- Mr Syme?

515
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,912
So soon? Vital signs?

516
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:02,152
- All normal.
- What have you done to Tom?

517
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:05,118
I told you we had a cure,
what do you think we've done?

518
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:08,158
- You're going to cure him?
- No, we've already cured him.

519
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:10,356
- We should take Mrs Jackman with us.
- Why?

520
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:12,715
- Because she's entitled.
- What about them?

521
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:15,633
- They'll have to stay here.
- Why?

522
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:21,238
No, it's OK, you go, see your husband.
We'll see you again shortly.

523
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:22,400
Yeah.

524
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:25,232
Yeah, see you.

525
00:43:26,240 --> 00:43:30,552
Bloody shame, actually.
You should have been working for me.

526
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:33,757
- You said I had nothing.
- Oh, nothing at all, really,

527
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:37,037
but you were so close.

528
00:43:37,200 --> 00:43:42,718
But... if... if Henry Jekyll
had no descendants,

529
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:46,634
if Tom Jackman isn't a clone,
then where did he come from?

530
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:51,874
I was hoping you were going to tell us,
because we don't have the faintest idea.

531
00:45:25,120 --> 00:45:26,120
<i>Daddy?</i>

532
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:32,755
<i>Is that you, Daddy?</i>

533
00:45:35,280 --> 00:45:36,952
<i>Are you my daddy?</i>

534
00:45:40,720 --> 00:45:43,837
<i>Did you want to know</i>
<i>what I look like, Daddy?</i>

535
00:45:45,120 --> 00:45:47,156
<i>You did, didn't you?</i>

536
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:51,719
<i>What do you think? Are you proud?</i>

537
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:57,277
<i>What do you look like, Daddy?</i>

538
00:45:57,440 --> 00:46:01,672
<i>Are you old? Are you really, really old?</i>

539
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:06,672
<i>You feel old. I can feel you in here.</i>

540
00:46:06,840 --> 00:46:10,435
<i>Feel your thoughts. Old, dusty thoughts.</i>

541
00:46:10,600 --> 00:46:13,239
<i>Old and scared.</i>

542
00:46:14,400 --> 00:46:16,914
<i>Always so scared.</i>

543
00:46:17,080 --> 00:46:20,390
<i>Why are you so scared, Daddy?</i>

544
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:25,355
<i>Are you scared of me?</i>

545
00:46:29,643 --> 00:46:30,857
<i>Are you married?</i>

546
00:46:31,010 --> 00:46:33,962
<i>Do I have a mummy?</i>

547
00:46:35,680 --> 00:46:38,274
<i>Or are you alone?</i>

548
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:40,635
<i>You feel alone.</i>

549
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,030
<i>You think alone.</i>

550
00:46:43,880 --> 00:46:47,031
<i>I can feel what you think.</i>

551
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:50,030
<i>Think of a number.</i>

552
00:46:50,200 --> 00:46:54,876
<i>No, do it Daddy, think of a number.</i>
<i>A big silly number, go on, it's a game.</i>

553
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:57,600
<i>Say it out loud, a big fat number,</i>
<i>any big fat number.</i>

554
00:46:57,760 --> 00:46:59,432
- 103.
<i>- 103.</i>

555
00:46:59,600 --> 00:47:01,431
Oh, God!

556
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:04,114
<i>I was right, wasn't I?</i>

557
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:07,192
<i>Bet I was.</i>

558
00:47:09,738 --> 00:47:10,900
<i>Waaah!</i>

559
00:47:11,520 --> 00:47:13,556
<i>I'm in your head.</i>

560
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:17,474
<i>I know what you think.</i>
<i>I am what you think.</i>

561
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:20,029
<i>Scared now, aren't you, Daddy?</i>
<i>Scaredy Daddy.</i>

562
00:47:20,200 --> 00:47:21,315
I'm not scared of you!

563
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,710
<i>Yes, you are.</i>

564
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:30,393
<i>I'm coming to get you, Daddy.</i>

565
00:47:30,560 --> 00:47:33,518
<i>I'm coming to eat you, Daddy.</i>

566
00:47:46,320 --> 00:47:49,949
<i>Oh, you've got
a vivid imagination, Daddy.</i>

567
00:47:50,920 --> 00:47:54,071
<i>I've been there.</i>

568
00:47:57,640 --> 00:47:59,073
You, shut up.

569
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:03,717
Shut up! Shut up!

570
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:04,880
Shut up!

571
00:48:06,858 --> 00:48:08,348
Shut up!

572
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:31,591
Just a moment.

573
00:48:40,640 --> 00:48:44,713
- Who is it?
- Delivery, sir.

574
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:50,079
- I didn't order anything.
- 6 Stadler Street? Dr Jackman?

575
00:48:50,240 --> 00:48:53,550
You phoned yesterday,
said it was an emergency.

576
00:49:00,880 --> 00:49:04,395
New television, sir.

577
00:49:04,800 --> 00:49:07,109
Do you want some help opening the box?

578
00:49:18,600 --> 00:49:20,989
Why is he in that box?

579
00:49:21,160 --> 00:49:23,833
It's the only way to keep him stable.

580
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,958
They'll be ready for us in a moment,
uh... Coffee?

581
00:49:27,120 --> 00:49:29,918
- Could someone get some coffee?
- Why now?

582
00:49:30,080 --> 00:49:32,469
You've had a cure
for over 50 years, you said.

583
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:35,438
Because your husband...

584
00:49:37,600 --> 00:49:39,795
Claire...

585
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:42,428
Tom's dying.

586
00:49:42,600 --> 00:49:46,593
Every change is shredding his DNA.
He won't see 45.

587
00:49:46,760 --> 00:49:50,309
He may not even see the end of the
month. We couldn't wait any longer.

588
00:49:50,480 --> 00:49:51,913
- We wanted to.
- Why?

589
00:49:52,080 --> 00:49:55,072
- He's all yours in a minute.
- Thank you.

590
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:57,603
- Why did you want to wait?
- We know how to stabilise him

591
00:49:57,723 --> 00:50:00,154
and we've always known
how to stop the changes,

592
00:50:00,320 --> 00:50:04,518
but we didn't know
in which form he'd stabilise.

593
00:50:04,680 --> 00:50:06,671
- It's Hyde we want.
- I don't want Hyde.

594
00:50:07,004 --> 00:50:08,070
I know.

595
00:50:09,520 --> 00:50:11,511
- Watch out, it's hot.
- Go away.

596
00:50:11,680 --> 00:50:13,398
It's all right.

597
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:15,915
Who is he now?

598
00:50:16,720 --> 00:50:19,757
How do you know which one he's...

599
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:22,480
stabilised as?

600
00:50:22,640 --> 00:50:24,471
We open the box.

601
00:50:24,640 --> 00:50:27,154
And then what?

602
00:50:27,320 --> 00:50:31,916
Either you take Dr Jackman home,
or Mr Hyde stays here.

603
00:50:32,080 --> 00:50:36,596
- They're both my husband.
- No, no, no, Hyde is ours.

604
00:50:39,840 --> 00:50:40,840
I see.

605
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:46,151
Well, then.

606
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:50,709
I'll have that coffee, thanks.

607
00:50:51,760 --> 00:50:53,876
I'd wish you luck,
but you wouldn't believe me.

608
00:50:54,040 --> 00:50:55,678
It's not an even chance, is it?

609
00:50:55,840 --> 00:50:58,229
You wouldn't be doing this if it was.

610
00:50:59,080 --> 00:51:01,913
You think it's Hyde in there.

611
00:51:02,080 --> 00:51:05,277
- They do.
- You don't?

612
00:51:05,440 --> 00:51:09,399
At every stage of this, Tom's been
stronger than anyone ever expected.

613
00:51:09,560 --> 00:51:12,677
- I'd never bet against him.
- You sound like you're proud of him.

614
00:51:12,840 --> 00:51:16,355
- He's my friend.
- Yes.

615
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:18,715
He's your friend.

616
00:51:21,960 --> 00:51:23,029
- How hot?
- Very hot.

617
00:51:23,200 --> 00:51:26,112
- Thanks.
- Arrgh! Jesus Christ!

618
00:51:26,280 --> 00:51:29,670
- I apologise for the coffee.
- Well, then, what are you waiting for?

619
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:33,549
- Get my husband out of that bloody box!
- Shit!

